---
description: Backend FastAPI rules
globs:
  - "backend/**/*.py"
---

Backend conventions:
- Use FastAPI routers.
- Use Pydantic schemas for request/response models.
- Separate route, schema, service, and repository layers.
- Keep business logic out of route handlers.
- Use type hints everywhere.
- Write pytest tests for new behavior.
- Use clear HTTP status codes.
- Do not access storage directly from route handlers.